{"type":"message","id":"124d5f32","parentId":"ff0cd272","timestamp":"2026-05-11T12:06:19.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user (เจ้านาย) wants to push everything to GitHub so he can clone it onto the Mac Pro 2013. This makes sense - use Git as the sync mechanism.\n\nLet me think about what needs to happen:\n\n1. Check if there's already a git repo in owen-workspace\n2. Figure out what should be committed and what should NOT be committed\n3. Help set up the GitHub repo\n\nFirst, I need to check the current state of the workspace. But also, I need to be careful about:\n- Secrets / API keys - should NOT be in git\n- MODEL_FORMAT_LOCK.md - protected, can't touch without password\n- Any sensitive data\n\nLet me first check the workspace structure and git status. Also need to follow the workspace rules - code/config work requires SocratiCode first, but this is more of a git setup task.\n\nActually, per AGENTS.md rules:\n- Code/config tasks need SocratiCode first\n- But this is more of a git/devops task\n\nLet me also check what's already in gitignore or if git is initialized.\n\nAlso important: there may be secrets, API keys, tokens etc that should NOT go to GitHub. Need to check for those.\n\nLet me think about the flow:\n1. Check workspace git status\n2. Check for sensitive files\n3. Create/modify .gitignore\n4. Initialize git if needed\n5. Push to GitHub\n\nI should proceed step by step but efficiently. Let me check the current state first.\n\nOne concern: the user mentioned \"กูจะทำการ เชื่อมข้อมูลทุกอย่างลงgithub\" - they want to connect everything to GitHub. I should help them set this up.\n\nLet me check:\n- Is git initialized?\n- Are there sensitive files?\n- What's the directory structure?\n\nI'll check git status and look at the directory for .gitignore first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"ทำงาน: ตรวจสอบสถานะ git ใน workspace และไฟล์ที่ควร/ไม่ควร push"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vk26